\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\kerning2\loch\af31506\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af31507 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1966198 \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
You now know what the Scarlet King is. He is a creation of swirling anomalies, of so many different times, all over the world. He is the memory of a world that is lost, the premodern world, made manifest in a form of hatred for modernity, the new, the hum
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 a\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
nism and smiling coldness that marks our day to day existence. Forged from a perfect balance of irreconcilable anomalies and our breaking minds. He is an entity created by this overwhelming, unavoidable tension. Of the howl of the old world when faced wit
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 h a cold, grey, purposeless new. He is the revenge of our fallen past. He is the idea of the ancient in a world which discards and fetishes it.\tab \hich\f31506 \'84
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 ~ Dipesh Spivak on the Scarlet King in Tufto's Proposal.\tab 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
The Scarlet King is one of the main antagonists of the SCP Foundation series. He is an ancient and evil god worshiped by groups such as the Children of the Scarlet King as a ruthless powerful monarch often tied to the destruction of the current world as w
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 e know it.
\par 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
He serves as the overarching antagonist behind the articles SCP-231 and possibly SCP-2317, and the main antagonist of the "Operation MAGNOLIA" series. He is one of the many anomalies proposed for the title of "SCP-001", an entry originally written for the
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506  2018 Doomsday Contest.
\par 
