\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Appearance
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
In the tale "Three Short Scenes About Death" the Scarlet King is given a little description. His fist are described as massive and gnarled, holding the chains of his consorts and concubines. The same fists could effortlessly smash a man's throat. The King
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
's voice is described as similar to "the chittering of a billion infinitesimal insects", and swirling and constantly moving. His voice also was neither "high nor low nor cacophonous nor methodical", simply just being. When the Scarlet King first appeared 
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 to\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
 the Serpent, he took the form of a girl in red clothes sitting on a rocking throne. On other occasions, the Scarlet King was depicted as a gigantic monstrous red whale that swam through the watery abyss, devoured everything in his path and dominated the 
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 food chain.
\par 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
According to Tufto's SCP-001 Proposal, the King is more akin to a living idea than an individual entity; in effect, he is the idea of nihilism, the people's dissatisfaction with the modern way of life, and can assimilate an entity thought to be him into a
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
n aspect of himself just as it did with SCP-2317-K. He is always depicted as figure with a crown-like ornament over his head showing royalty and associated with the color red, or in the cases of alien cultures lacking the perception of the color red the K
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 in\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
g would be associated with a color that would be synonymous or close with the color. In SCP-4989, Dr. Simon Kells described looking at the King "like staring at a Pattern Screamer only more hollow".
\par 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
When a group of Foundation agents confronted the physical form of the Scarlet King in his supposed throne room, he appeared as a young malnourished boy with hanging messy hair, crimson red eyes, wearing only a tunic and beaten sandals, and covered in bloo
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 d\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
, having taken the form of the first child who was sacrificed in his name. Drawn to the chaos caused during the Manhattan Crisis, the Scarlet King manifested himself as a false garden attempting to imitate nature, before battling SCP-2912-JP at which poin
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
t he transformed into a headless humanoid with no lower body that was solely comprised of bones, fangs, organs, and blood vessels, while surrounded by seven rays of light that could form into gigantic hands and emitting laughing and screams resembling tho
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 se\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506  of a baby.
\par 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
In "Dr. Wondertainment Goes Out With A Bang", the Scarlet King was described as having an anorexic thin humanoid body, standing exactly seven feet tall and emitting blinding red light. His skin resembled that of a burnt corpse, his hands were gnarled claw
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 s, and possessed two great antlers behind his head and multiple eyes on his face. When confronting Cornelius Wondertainment he wore a military uniform covered in medals and rank markers.
\par 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
In SCP-5641, the Scarlet King was described as ten trillion times Skanda's size, possessing seven mouths which spoke profanities, eyes that killed anyone who looked into them, and fourteen hands which he used to form all types of mudras. In SCP-6765, the 
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 King's body was described as a humanoid with a bleeding red maw surrounded by grasping arms and eyes while clouded by smoke and fire, and poured endless blood and released an endless inhumane scream.
\par 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
In ROUNDERHOUSE's Jade Proposal, the Scarlet King was depicted as a gigantic androgynous red humanoid being with an obscured face and always accompanying his avatar who was depicted as a sleeping man with a long beard, an elaborate headdress and carrying 
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
long spears across his back. When approached by Greaves the Scarlet King took the form of a vast red sea, and when he took possession of the lieutenant, manifested at first as Greaves' nervous system glowing red before taking the appearance of a 3 meter t
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 al\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 l skinless humanoid with a bare skull, large horns resting atop his head and inscribed with pulsating symbols and markings.
\par 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Personality
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
The Scarlet King as an old god from the Abyss was shown to be a cruel, manipulative, greedy and selfish individual, though this was more of an image he held to his insecurity and cowardice. After coming into contact with the Tree of Life, he wished to mak
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 e\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
 all of it his property, and if he were to fail then he would destroy existence so no one else would claim it. He became hellbent on conquering everything, especially the Tree of Life, by any means necessary, enslaving and devouring numerous gods and doin
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
g whatever pleased him. It is believed that if SCP-999 were to interact with the Scarlet King, then his heart would change and finally see the beauty of the world and abandon his quest of destruction. However, that turned out to be all a lie fabricated by
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506  a\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506  maddened O5. It was noted that the Scarlet King was always honest, instead having his subjects lie on his behalf.
\par 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
In Tufto's Proposal, however, it is shown that the Scarlet King has no true personality of his own, instead his nature being shaped by the belief of humanity. Because the Indians became furious at the British colonizers for studying and categorizing their
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506  \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
