\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 But to destroy her would destroy everything he believed.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 So await the 13th he did.\tab \hich\f31506 \'84
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 ~ Excerpt from the Finnfolk Penumbra in the "Seas of Orcadia Hub".\tab 
\par \loch\af31506\dbch\af31505\hich\f31506 \'93\tab \loch\f31506 
Behind her, there is something she feels before seeing, something warm and safe that calms her shaking frame, even though it doesn't have anything like a form. Just a sense that things will be all right, that she's not alone, no matter how much she thin
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 k\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
s she is. Surrounded by a crimson light, she has a sense of peace and purpose that she doesn't understand in the least. That there's a storm just beyond her sight and it's coming, but she's not alone.\tab \hich\f31506 \'84
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 ~ Lucy being comforted in her dreams by her father Lucian Greaves in "I Think I Could Be Brave".\tab 
\par \loch\af31506\dbch\af31505\hich\f31506 \'93\tab \loch\f31506 
Righteous Angel, made eunuch by the blades of Canaan, lead the flock to righteousness. Your boneless benevolence is the guiding star of the True Children of Israel. Let not their half-breed Antichrist rise from his tomb to devour the world once more. We
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506  know you shall not fail us, for through God, all things are possible.\tab \hich\f31506 \'84
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 ~ A prayer to the Scarlet King from "Christ In Scarlet - Hub".\tab 
\par \loch\af31506\dbch\af31505\hich\f31506 \'93\tab \loch\f31506 Now ahead, I see a Scarlet King.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 His horns shape a violent red crown.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 He holds out his jagged right hand,
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 And cuts it, giving me new life.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Bring justice upon the damned.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 He kneels, wrapping around me his gown.
\par 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Cried, I did. Soon, I shall sing.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Our gift to you, these lovely flames.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 O, your screams are like a song!
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Just before we broke your foul lords,
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 The Ambassador cast us out.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 In this place, there were great hoards.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 The fools thought themselves as strong,
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Yet it is their blood that rains.
\par 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Their warm blood drops me to weep.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Father holds me like an infant.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 In my ear, he hums a tune:
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Rest now, my darling child.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 He whispers, under the moon.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Soon, my cries go distant
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 And I drift into a soft sleep.\tab \hich\f31506 \'84
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 ~ The Scarlet King comforting and empowering a poor Alagaddan slave in "Heart Filled".\tab 
\par \loch\af31506\dbch\af31505\hich\f31506 \'93\tab \loch\f31506 You will gain freedom through violence. Just like your father.\tab \hich\f31506 \'84
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 ~ SCP-8166-2's persona as the Scarlet King speaking to her in "Dreams of Crimson and Azure".\tab 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Other Media
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 In Music
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 The Australian-based band known as the Atomic Beau Project released on March 23, 2019, a song based on the Scarlet King and SCP-2317 titled "The King".
\par 
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 Trivia
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 The concept of the Scarlet King was originally created by author DrClef in SCP-231, but the character was properly developed by other authors such as Djoric, Tufto and UraniumEmpire.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 DrClef when creating both SCP-231 and SCP-2317 was partially inspired by the now-deleted version of SCP-363 titled "Tree-Like Horns" which had been based on "The Walkers" painting by Justin Cherry.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
Tufto has regretted several decisions he took when writing the SCP-001 Proposal, since it has been misinterpreted as being a criticism for modernity, similar to a postmodernist view, but in truth it was meant to be about the inability to let go of the fla
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 wed outdated past.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 The Scarlet King has been influenced by numerous entities across religion, mythology and fiction, with some being: The Devil, Abaddon, the Leviathan, Typhon, Chernobog, Hastur, the Crimson King, Ahriman, Khorne and Z
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\insrsid1966198 \loch\af1\dbch\af31505\hich\f1 \u804\'3f\u834\'3f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af42 \ltrch\fcs0 \f42\insrsid1966198 \loch\af42\dbch\af31505\hich\f42 \'e2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\insrsid1966198 
\loch\af1\dbch\af31505\hich\f1 \u802\'3f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \f37\insrsid1966198 \loch\af37\dbch\af31505\hich\f37 \u7735\'3f\u842\'3f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af31507 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1966198 \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f1\insrsid1966198 \loch\af1\dbch\af31505\hich\f1 \u825\'3f\u787\'3f\loch\af1\dbch\af31505\hich\f1 \u559\'3f\u792\'3f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af31507 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1966198 .
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
Given that the Scarlet King was revealed in Tufto's Proposal to be the embodiment of the conflict between premodernity and modernity created by human thought, this makes him similar to the Idea of Evil from Berserk. The Scarlet King's depiction in SCP-646
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 2\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
 and "Omnigenesis and the Law of Blades" was based off Jagganoth from Kill Six Billion Demons. The Scarlet King's portrayal in "Tears and Bone" was based on Edgar Allan Poe's story Hop-Frog. In ROUNDERHOUSE's Jade Proposal, the Scarlet shares similarities
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506  with Azathoth as both beings could create a world and life from their dreams alone, with the difference being that the Scarlet King is much weaker and willingly slumbered for his dreams to maintain Korar.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
The Scarlet King is often theorized to possibly be the true or final stage of SCP-2317-K, an untold horror that even the SCP Foundation has difficulty containing and documenting. Since the wiki has no real canon, it is ultimately up to the reader to belie
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 ve if SCP-2317 and the Scarlet King are one and the same. However, 2317's creator personally believes that it and the Scarlet King are completely separate entities.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
SCP-3806-A claims that Yaldabaoth and the Scarlet King are known to snatch human souls in the astral plane. She also suggests that Odin is also gathering honorable souls to form an army in order to fight either the Scarlet King or Yaldabaoth in the end of
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506  times.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 The Scarlet King is often associated with whales. This is because the author Djoric joked about SCP-231-7's race being redacted and that since it was five letters long she could have been a whale instead of a human.

\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
In the universe of SCP-6001 where the Compendium, a benevolent amalgam organization of different GoIs, took over the world and declared worldwide peace with all anomalies, it is mentioned that they were capable of vanquishing and probably even killing the
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506  Scarlet King and his pantheon.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 In the joke tale "Tim Wilson KILLS THE MARVEL UNIVERSE!!!", the Scarlet King is one of the many notable beings killed off-screen by Tim Wilson of Wilson's Wildlife Solutions.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
In the comedic tale "Dust and Shopper's Rewards", the Scarlet King goes shopping at Walmart in order to provide food for his daughter/wife, and there, he also meets O5-1 who informs the King on how 231-7 was doing. After he became annoyed with the service
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506  of the store, the Scarlet King tried to leave before realizing that he became trapped there in a similar manner to SCP-3008.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 In the year 3870 A.D. in the universe of Earth-7M, the Scarlet King was able to manifest himself in that reality and proceeded to have intercourse with the universe's sun.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 In Djoric's headcanon, SCP-682, SCP-879 and SCP-058 are the spawn of the Scarlet King, while SCP-999 is nothing more than the still-living placenta of one of the spawn.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
According to "A Contingency, if this Wonderful World Doesn't Happen", if "What a Wonderful World" were to be continued as planned it would have been revealed that the Scarlet King was using Isabel Wondertainment V as a vessel after the universe was recrea
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
ted and he converted into the idea of progress as a result of representing the ever-present human ambition. Under the influence of the King Isabel would become a ruthless extremist leading a revolution against The Factory and later the Foundation and its 
\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 al\hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 
lies, wanting to abolish the Veil of Secrecy and force humanity to progress even if it costs the lives of the non-notable and weaker individuals. This story would've been influenced by Animal Farm.
\par \hich\af31506\dbch\af31505\loch\f31506 According to Sammy Skipper, the Scarlet King's appearance as a vague humanoid being with antlers is not his true appearance but an hallucination by the human mind trying to comprehend his true form.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
